commit_list.message:
Fix for when CLASSPATH environment path is set

Say, I had a CLASSPATH of:
export CLASSPATH=opsin-big-0.1.0.jar
rcdk would concatenate that directly to form a classpath of
opsin-big-0.1.0.jarfilelocation/../java/lib/cdk-1.2 ...
giving no colon separation in the path.

This just puts that colon there.
In the case where the classpath is empty, there's an extra colon, but I
don't think that matters.

Increase limit for smallest ring size

Story: I have a PDB I want to read into RDKit. It has a disulfide bond
between two cysteines ~400 residues apart. This creates a very large
ring. RDKit throws an error because the number of found rings is less
than the expected number of rings. The ring wasn't found because RDKit
thought all "smallest" rings should be 256 or smaller.

Now, as long as your ring is UINT_MAX aka 4,294,967,295 or smaller, life
is beautiful. I hope no one has a ring bigger than 4 billion atoms.
use print function in FindNumpy.cmake for python3 compatibility

Find Python Library corresponding to PYTHON_EXECUTABLE

If a system devel packages for both python 2 and 3,
cmake can find an executable for python 2 and library
for python 3, now it looks for a library that corresponds
to the executables

Before (python 2 executable, python3.4 library):
$ cmake -LAH .. | grep '^PYTHON_[EL][XI]'
PYTHON_EXECUTABLE:FILEPATH=/usr/bin/python
PYTHON_LIBRARY:FILEPATH=/usr/lib64/libpython3.4m.so

After:
$ cmake -LAH .. | grep '^PYTHON_[EL][XI]'
PYTHON_EXECUTABLE:FILEPATH=/usr/bin/python
PYTHON_LIBRARY:FILEPATH=/usr/lib64/libpython2.7.so

will give you no conformers for molecule with zero rotatable
bonds, so the molecule disappears. This makes confab return the
original coordinates if there are zero rotatable bonds.
